Basic docker setup:

To compile a docker image of Kismet:
    $ docker build -t kismet-git .

To run a Kismet which accepts remote connections:
    $ docker run -p 2501:2501 -p 3501:3501 --name kismet kismet-git

To run a Kismet docker which can handle local interfaces
directly, you will need to run it in privileged mode:
    $ docker run -p 2501:2501 -p 3501:3501 --name kismet --privileged kismet-git

You can then assign interfaces to it using the included script,
assign_wifi_to_docker.sh:
    $ $ sudo ./assign_wifi_to_docker.sh kismet wlx4494fcf30eb3

